text: 2-Phenyl-3,5-dimethylmorpholine is a drug with stimulant and anorectic effects, related to phenmetrazine. Based on what is known from other phenylmorpholines with similar structure, it likely acts as a norepinephrine- dopamine releasing agent and may produce effects similar or slightly different to phenmetrazine. == See also == * 3-Fluorophenmetrazine * G-130 (2-Phenyl-5,5-dimethylmorpholine) * 3,4-Phendimetrazine (2-Phenyl-3,4-dimethylmorpholine) * 3,6-Phendimetrazine (2-Phenyl-3,6-dimethylmorpholine) * Manifaxine * Radafaxine * Viloxazine Category:Anorectics Category:Stimulants
title: PDM-35
